history.text: I loved this movie. What did you think?
It was funny, but slightly spiritual
I guess it's one of those movies that critics will pan as bad, but a casual observer will enjoy very much.
What did you think of Jim Carrey's performance?
Jim Carey usually thrives very well in the physical type of humor. This movie fits his style very well. What did you think of Morgan Freeman's performance?
Morgan Freeman Is an exceptional actor,and the role of God, fit him perfectly
What did you think of the scene when he makes the other anchor act crazy? Steve Carrell killed that scene
I thought that was comedic genius!
Do you think that Jim Carrey did a good job playing God?

I think Jim Carey played the role well in the sense he was a human being playing God. He captured that child like elation followed by the heavy burden that must be carried. I feel he had that serious undertone that many people will question if they can do it.
Did you feel Jennifer Aniston was a good role as his wife?
Yes, her and Jim Carrey make an excellent team onscreen
But the fact that he had feelings for his coworker kind of offsets the romance part of the movie
Do you feel this movie was trying to teach a lesson?
Yes, I do. God, as an all powerful being has a lot on his hands, and most people don't know the amount of work that is involved
But Bruce Nolan got to experience that for himself and actually realize that it's a lot of work
